  "prompt": "If I live in NYC but work on Long Island do I have to pay city income tax?",
  "response": "Yes, if you live in New York City, you are subject to NYC resident income tax, regardless of where you work, including Long Island. NYC resident income tax applies to all residents, and it is separate from state income tax. Your employer's location does not affect this tax obligation. You will need to file and pay NYC income taxes on your income as a resident of the city.",
